6. Elegantius quam necesse est probae] The ancient Romans regarded dancing and. singing as accomplishments exhibited for the entertainment of others. Hence they were always connected in their minds with servile or histrionic per- formanees. The fashion of dancing for amusement, or to contribute to social festivity among themselves, was learnt at a later period from the Greeks.
